On Mon, Dec 22, 2003 at 06:10:44PM -0800, Mike Soultanian wrote:
> solid lifters/cam.  My thinking is that yes, it requires constant
> adjustment, however (due to my lazy nature) it forces me to check my
> valves regularly with helps me to quickly identify if there are any
> irregularities if adjustments go out of whack. 

funny thing is with hydraulic, you CANT check the valves. No
indication for you if you have a slowly dropping valve, or a valve
stem stretching. So even if you were so inclined and built your new
engine w/ hyd you could not check them :(

